<p>If we use <code class="highlighter-rouge">diff bye.sh hi.sh</code> the output looks like this:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">1c1
&lt; <span class="c">#!/usr/bin/env bash</span>
<span class="nt">---</span>
<span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="c">#!/bin/sh</span>
3c3
&lt; <span class="k">function </span>bye<span class="o">(){</span>
<span class="nt">---</span>
<span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="k">function </span>hi<span class="o">(){</span>
5c5
&lt;   <span class="nb">printf</span> <span class="s2">"%s</span><span class="se">\n</span><span class="s2">"</span> <span class="s2">"Bye, </span><span class="k">${</span><span class="nv">t</span><span class="p">^</span><span class="k">}</span><span class="s2">!"</span>
<span class="nt">---</span>
<span class="o">&gt;</span>   <span class="nb">printf</span> <span class="s2">"%s</span><span class="se">\n</span><span class="s2">"</span> <span class="s2">"Hi, </span><span class="k">${</span><span class="nv">t</span><span class="p">^</span><span class="k">}</span><span class="s2">!"</span>
8c8
&lt; bye <span class="nv">$1</span>
<span class="nt">---</span>
<span class="o">&gt;</span> hi <span class="nv">$1</span></code></pre></figure>

<p>A little difficult to visualize, right ?!</p>

<p>Already with <code class="highlighter-rouge">meld bye.sh hi.sh</code></p>

